Document: @GlobalScope  
Path: godot/classes/class_@globalscope.rst  
Summary: The @GlobalScope class represents the global scope in Godot, serving as a placeholder for scripts that need to access global variables or functions.  

@GlobalScope is a built-in class that inherits from Object. It is used as a contextual placeholder when writing scripts that require access to global variables or functions, though it does not contain any actual functionality itself. This class is primarily relevant in code completion and documentation contexts rather than runtime execution.
---CHUNK---
